The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning from demonstrations, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses the concept of the Zone of Proximal Development (ZPD), which is a concept from educational psychology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses Atari games as a testbed, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses teaching strategies, which could also place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
